(20, '<p>Summons No: KBR/31301/2013/0417</p>\r\n<p><strong>Jeffrey Bin Zaidi </strong></p>\r\n<p>Vs.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Sara Urusharta Sdn. Bhd</strong></p>', '<p>Encik Jeffrey Zaidi on 16 August 2011 was involved in a fight with a friend after office hours at Masjid Bahagian Kuching area as he was accused of causing grievous injury by his victim. Subsequently he was arrested by the police and was remanded under Section 324 of Penal Code. He was charged and convicted for causing grievous hurt and sentenced to 2 years imprisonment. His appeal to High Court was dismissed. His appeal against conviction was dismissed by the Court of Appeal but the Court Allowed his appeal against sentence by reducing his with imprisonment to 28 days with effect from 7 February 2013 and fine of RM5,000.00.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; On 25/7/2013, disciplinary committee was formed.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; On 18/10/2013, Disciplinary Committee decided to dismiss Jeffrey Zaidi pursuant to Regulation 28(3) of the Statutory Bodies Disciplinary Regulations. His appeal to Disciplinary Action Committee was dismissed.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; Encik Jeffrey Zaidi complained to Labour office in Kuching pursuant to his termination on 14/10/2103 by SUSB,claiming:</p>\r\n<p>&bull; Gaji Ganti Notis amounting RM3,223.10; and</p>\r\n<p>&bull; Termination Benefits RM17,047.80.</p>', '<p>&bull; Encik Jeffrey denied that the fight was happened outside office hours and it is only considered as incident.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; Futher, he sends the appeal letter to SUSB on 21/10/2013 informed that he was not satisfied with the Disciplinary Committee decision against him.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; Among other his appeal was:</p>\r\n<p>a) SUSB should give him three (3) months&rsquo; notice of termination;</p>\r\n<p>b) SUSB should give him compensation as per agreed to him by verbally; and</p>\r\n<p>c) SUSB to continue paying his salary until December 2013.</p>', '<ul>\r\n<li>Case Pending</li>\r\n</ul>', 'General', 'maps', '2016-01-27 15:06:17');

